The faction is most likely Rogue Clockworks, meaning those that have defected from the Gnomes and line a free lifestyle that usually involves killing newbies. Most clockworks in the city are friends of the Gem Choppers- Gnome warriors/ guards. It is a very good idea to learn which faction is which, and learn the in game name for guild, groups, and the like. just like the Felwithe caster (and thus Mage) guild are the Art Keepers, most have a name that is identical to thier faction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jayteebushwacker>Jaytee Bushwacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Summoner Da'FoH</span><br>  Posts: 1423<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/03 12:51:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=26>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Well...I took your advice and started off to Qeynos!</span><hr size=1> If you haven't ruined your clockwork faction already you can ask the guides to show you around the gnome city.  Its actually kinda cool you can do that =) I remember doing it way way back in my day.<br>
