I left Freeport and somehow ended up in the desert. THEN I zoned to some Oasis place...THERE an Orc Priest attacked and killed me and *poof* I was back at Felwithe! Pfft<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Use bind (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/spells/spell.asp?Id=228" target="top">Bind Affinity</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->) as soon as you can (at lv 12) and use it all the time. As a young 'un and new to the game it is very easy to die and there is nothing more annoying than running over a continent, just to die and have to do it again. Untill lv 12 use the soul binders, which are located in every town. Just walk up to the soul binder, target and say 'bind my soul'. Next time you die, that will be the spot where you pop back into the world. It is also the spot you will return to when using the spell gate. At lv 12 you get bind affinity, which basically allows you to bind yourself mor or less evryware (with some exceptions) and other players in towns and some other spots. It is a small art form to select a good spot to bind, but generally people bind in the closest city (or with planes of power in plane of knowledge).<br>
<br>
It is a good idea to have gate memorised all the time, because it can be used as an emergency escape.<br>
<br>
OOhh, and one thing, once you hit lv 10, you will NOT pop back into the world with your equipment, but rather with nothing at all at the spot where you were binded, and you will have to spend time locating the corpse to get your stuff back.<br>
 <p>nmee - commander of mudhills<br>
